ly here, Mum.'</p><p>\"On Friday I was out buying Christmas presents for Dylan and his big brother Jake who is eight. I got a garbled message on my answerphone from my daughter. She was almost incoherent. I called her back and she told me what had happened. She kept saying: 'Mum, how do you tell an eight-year-old his six-year-old brother is dead and not coming back?'\"'</p><p>Moretti said Jake was also at the school on Friday and heard the gunfire, adding that the family lived almost opposite Lanza and his mother.</p><p>The UK Foreign and Commonwealth Office said it did not comment on consular cases involving children.</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/401159731|2012-12-22T11:49:04Z|2d404f5367aa6b7d4516d5d42b2f3e9d0c5c6c72 -->","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2012-12-17T01:25:01Z","hasStoryPackage":"true","score":"1.0","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/12/16/1355674125051/Dylan-Hockley-006.jpg","standfirst":"Six-year-old boy whose family moved to Connecticut from Hampshire is revealed to be among those killed","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3chbj","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/12/16/1355674125051/Dylan-Hockley-006.jpg","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"401159731","internalOctopusCode":"7031580","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"James Meikle","publication":"guardian.co.uk","newspaperEditionDate":"2012-12-17","internalPageCode":"1843228","shouldHideAdverts":"true","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2012-12-19T14:29:04Z"},"tags":[{"id":"world/newtown-shooting","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news","webTitle":"Newtown shooting","webUrl":"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/newtown-shooting","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/world/newtown-shooting","references":[]},{"id":"world/gun-crime","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news","webTitle":"Gun crime","webUrl":"http://w